{%- comment -%}
  Free-shipping progress bar.

  Renders a subtotal-to-threshold progress bar when the merchant has
  configured a free-shipping minimum via `settings.kt_free_shipping_threshold`
  (in the shop's default currency, same integer units as Shopify prices
  — i.e. cents). When the merchant hasn't set one (0 or blank) the
  snippet renders nothing.

  States:
  - Under threshold: "Add {{ remaining }} more for free shipping" with
    a partially-filled bar
  - At/above threshold: "Free shipping unlocked" with a full bar
  - Digital-only cart (cart.requires_shipping == false): skip entirely
    — there's no shipping to unlock

  Used by main-cart.liquid (page) and cart-drawer.liquid (drawer).
  Snippet so the threshold math lives in one place.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  assign threshold = settings.kt_free_shipping_threshold | default: 0 | times: 1
  assign threshold_cents = threshold | times: 100
-%}

{%- if threshold_cents > 0 and cart.requires_shipping and cart.item_count > 0 -%}
  {%- comment -%}
    Use items_subtotal_price (pre-discount, pre-shipping line total)
    not total_price (post-discount, post-tax in EU/UK stores). Two
    reasons this matters for merchant-set "spend $X, get free shipping"
    thresholds:

    1. Discount codes: if a customer has a 20% coupon, cart.total_price
       is already discounted, so the bar unlocks free shipping before
       the customer hit the merchant-intended order size. Merchants set
       the threshold based on the GOODS amount, not the post-discount
       checkout total.
    2. Tax-included markets (UK, EU, AU, etc.): in tax_incl stores,
       cart.total_price includes VAT. A £50 threshold would unlock at
       ~£42 of pre-tax goods — again short of the merchant intent.

    items_subtotal_price is the sum of line_price × quantity before any
    cart-level discount or tax — exactly the figure merchants think in.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- assign subtotal = cart.items_subtotal_price -%}
  {%- if subtotal >= threshold_cents -%}
    {%- assign unlocked = true -%}
    {%- assign percent = 100 -%}
    {%- assign remaining_cents = 0 -%}
  {%- else -%}
    {%- assign unlocked = false -%}
    {%- assign percent = subtotal | times: 100 | divided_by: threshold_cents -%}
    {%- assign remaining_cents = threshold_cents | minus: subtotal -%}
  {%- endif -%}

  <div
    class="kt-free-ship {% if unlocked %}kt-free-ship--unlocked{% endif %}"
    role="status"
    aria-live="polite"
    data-free-shipping-bar
  >
    <p class="kt-free-ship__label">
      {%- if unlocked -%}
        {{ 'kt.cart.free_shipping.unlocked' | t | default: '🎉 Free shipping unlocked!' }}
      {%- else -%}
        {%- comment -%}
          Pre-format the money amount with the `| money` filter BEFORE
          handing it to `t:` — Liquid pipe precedence would otherwise
          apply `| money` to the whole translation string (which is
          not a number) and silently render the raw cents integer.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- assign remaining_formatted = remaining_cents | money -%}
        {{ 'kt.cart.free_shipping.remaining_html' | t: amount: remaining_formatted }}
      {%- endif -%}
    </p>
    <div class="kt-free-ship__track" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="kt-free-ship__fill" style="width: {{ percent }}%"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
{%- endif -%}
